title: Alaska Public Lands: Places To Go
body: Explore This Park    Plan Your Visit     Places to Go             Places To Go           photo nps/rf  Bore Tides An International Phenomenon They have been described as breaking waves as high as 26 feet, sounding like locomotive trains, foaming and frothing along at speeds between 6 and 24 miles per hour. Tidal bores are anything but BORING. Find out more with the Southcentral Alaska Bore Tide Information and Schedule.
